<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>T 444E Diesel Engine Diagnostics (NAVPAK) (1997) - SECTION 3.5: ELECTRONIC CONTROL SYSTEM DIAGNOSTICS,
        ACCELERATOR PEDAL POSITION SENSOR/IVS SWITCH (APS/IVS) - REMOTE PTO SPEED CONTROL (RPTO) - FAULT
        DETECTION/MANAGEMENT
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="PROCTYPE" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FAULT DETECTION/MANAGEMENT</title>
        <para>Disagreements in speed selection states will be detected by the ECM and a fault code will be set. The most
            common source of RPTO problems are blown fuses to the On/Off circuit, incorrectly programmed ECMs or wiring
            the body builder connectors and speed control switches improperly.
        </para>
        <para>Refer to
            <emph type="BOLD">Figure
                <hotlnk xrefid="f19017104">3.86</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the remote PTO speed control circuit diagram and
            <emph type="BOLD">Table
                <hotlnk xrefid="f19017105">3.30</hotlnk>
            </emph>
            for the connector checks.
        </para>
        <figure id="f19017104" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="eg1298" filename="../figeg1/EG1298.webp" type="webp"/>
            <caption>Figure 3.86 Remote PTO Speed Control Circuit Diagram</caption>
        </figure>
